cs.DC, cs.SE, cs.DS, cs.PL, cs.CC

This paper is focused on the comparison and evaluation of two techniques, OT and CRDT, for consistency maintenance in co-editors. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing). Additionally, the paper discusses the technical challenges, correctness, and complexity issues related to these techniques, which are relevant to software engineering (cs.SE), data structures (cs.DS), programming languages (cs.PL), and computational complexity (cs.CC).
